  "body": "[comment]: # (Please replace ... with your information. Remove < and >)\r\n\r\n### User Story\r\n\r\nAs a user, I don't want to inadvertently share my wallet address so that I can preserve my privacy.\r\n\r\n### Description\r\n\r\nWithin the \"+\" menu Status has an option to Invite Friends that invokes the system share sheet which sends a link to Status. The link contains a refCode that doesn't have any functionality and can unintentionally share the wallet address. We can remove this since it doesn't do anything. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nInviting friends sends the text \"Get Status at http://status.im\"\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nInviting friends sends the text \"Get Status at http://status.im?refCode=XXXXX\"\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\nHome > \"+\" > \"Invite friends > Message\r\n\r\n### Solution\r\nRemove the refcode \r\n\r\n### Additional Info\r\nThe 'invite friends' is a placeholder feature until we can create a seamless flow that helps users easily add/search/find/invite their friends.",
